us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFramePose2DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FramePose2DReadOnly, Pose2DBasics, Pose2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FramePose2DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FramePose2D

    public interface FixedFramePose2DBasics
extends FramePose2DReadOnly, Pose2DBasics
    Write and read interface for a 2D pose expressed in a constant reference frame, i.e. this pose is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Pose2DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFramePose2DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on poses occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FixedFramePose2DBasics extends Pose2DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Pose2DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFramePose2DBasics.

        default void prependRotation(FrameOrientation2DReadOnly orientation)

        If the rotation should not affect this pose's position, use Pose2DBasics.appendRotation(Orientation2DReadOnly).

        Parameters:
        orientation - the orientation to prepend to this pose 2D. Not modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and orientation are not expressed in the same reference frame.

      • prependTranslation

        default void prependTranslation(FrameTuple2DReadOnly translation)
        Adds the given translation to this pose 2D assuming it is expressed in the coordinates in which this pose is expressed.

        If the translation is expressed in the local coordinates described by this pose 2D, use appendTranslation(FrameTuple2DReadOnly).

        Parameters:
        translation - tuple containing the translation to apply to this pose 2D. Not modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and translation are not expressed in the same reference frame.

        Parameters:
        orientation - the orientation to append to this pose 2D. Not modified.

      • appendTranslation

        default void appendTranslation(FrameTuple2DReadOnly translation)
        Rotates, then adds the given translation to this pose 2D.

        Use this method if the translation is expressed in the local coordinates described by this pose 2D. Otherwise, use prependTranslation(FrameTuple2DReadOnly).

        Parameters:
        translation - tuple containing the translation to apply to this pose 2D. Not modified.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and translation are not expressed in the same reference frame.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(FramePose2DReadOnly other,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from this to other given the percentage alpha.

        this.position = (1.0 - alpha) * this.position + alpha * other.position
        this.orientation = (1.0 - alpha) * this.orientation + alpha * other.orientation

        Parameters:
        other - the other pose 2D used for the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage used for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in not modifying this, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this to other.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and other are not expressed in the same reference frame.

      • interpolate

        default void interpolate(FramePose2DReadOnly pose1,
                         Pose2DReadOnly pose2,
                         double alpha)
        Performs a linear interpolation from pose1 to pose2 given the percentage alpha.

        this.position = (1.0 - alpha) * pose1.position + alpha * pose2.position
        this.orientation = (1.0 - alpha) * pose1.orientation + alpha * pose2.orientation

        Parameters:
        pose1 - the first pose 2D used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        pose2 - the second pose 2D used in the interpolation. Not modified.
        alpha - the percentage to use for the interpolation. A value of 0 will result in setting this to pose1, while a value of 1 is equivalent to setting this to pose2.
        Throws:
        ReferenceFrameMismatchException - if this and pose1 are not expressed in the same reference frame.
